    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="cell-padding:0px; border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; cell-border-width:0px; border-style:none; background-color:#ccffcc; head-row-background-color:none; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="background-color:#ffffff;">
          <para styleclass="Body Text">There are two methods you can use to locate a <text styleclass="Element">Point*</text> in a <text styleclass="Element">Part.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Notes">NOTE: </text>These two methods relate to a <text styleclass="Element">Point</text> sketch-element, and a <text styleclass="Interface">start-Point</text>, <text styleclass="Interface">end-Point</text> and <text styleclass="Interface">centre-Point</text> in other sketch-elements.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Interface2">Method 1: <text styleclass="VariableName">Add Dimensions </text></para>
